#subtitle: Policies to address the economic crisis.

= Economic Policy

Turkish Economy is in a dire and unstable situation. As a developing and industrializing nation, Turkey depends on import substitution to fuel its expanding industry, in the meanwhile creating the necessity for a constant supply of foreign cash flowing in to cover the expenses of industrialization.

While this protectionism keeps the economy afloat, it has created a lazy industry uncapable of competing with other international competitors without state subsidies and high inflation as a result of the constant pressure on the Turkish Lira by the foreign currencies.

In its current state the Turkish economy is very volatile and dependent on the international economy. Drastic changes are needed before another wave strikes and crushes the ship that is the Turkish economy.

