max-visits: 3

Even though in the short term our citizens will suffer under higher prices, creating a surplus of foreign exchange is necessary for any real of the economy. Hopefully they will understand..

@export
choose-if: budget >= 2
subtitle: -2 Budget; Budget ↓↓; Inflation ↑; Exchange Pressure ↓↓; Growth ↑↑ 
on-arrival: forex_pressure -= 4; budget -= 2; inflation_modifier += 1.5; growth_modifier += 1.5; capitalists_CHP += 2; economicaction += 1

The Turkish capital has long lacked any sort of competitive capability against foreign companies. Through targetted subsidies for companies choosing to sell their goods abroad and bring in foreign currency, we can perhaps increase their competitiveness on the world stage and build an industry capable of surviving harsh crises. Though the subsidies are a burden on the budget, without making the Turkish industry competitive a permanent economic solution can not be achieved. 

@stateplanning
subtitle: Union relations slight decrease; Exchange Pressure ↓; Industrial Production ↑; Unemployment ↑
choose-if: imf_agreement == 0
unavailable-subtitle: We have agreed with the IMF to not pursue state interventions!
on-arrival: forex_pressure -= 2; disk_relation -= 4; industrial_production_index_modifier += 3; unemployment_modifier += 0.5; economicaction += 1

Turkey has a mixed market with huge state presence. However as these corporations tend to be heavily corrupt and misfunctioning, reforms getting rid of the inefficient employees and restructuring the outdated business models are necessary to uphold the economy as a whole.

